snippet.textDisplay: there so many design aspects that are fundamentally flawed. the blocking system doesn't make sense. you are supposed to try perfect parries, as the reward is breaking the opponents weapon. you still lose hp when not blocking perfectly, so on low hp you're getting punished for trying out the core principles. the regaining hp system is implemented poorly, so many bosses and mini bosses won't give you the window to recover the tiniest bit. the same problem occurs when you're trying to get the visceral attack after 'breaking' the posture. the enemies are just not affected at all, you have to be lucky to hit a charged attack, as the opponents poise is infinite. you need a proper window in the enemies combos, which are always longer than the window of posture break. all the problems get amplified by the delay in all the enemies attacks. it punishes reactions and encourages memorization. this game has a lot of potential, but at the same time it reminds me why fromsoft will sit on the throne for a while ...

For those who didn't play the demo. The deflection works like Sekiro's, it doesn't disbalance the enemy for a riposte like in BB.

Standard block: recoverable hp loss (easy but costly)
Perfect guard: no hp loss and build enemy's nonvisible stagger meter. eg. When the Watchman boss does a chain attack, chain deflections are needed. 

This is the core part of the game and everything else is built around it. The nerfed roll during lock on is to encourage deflection.
